# Phase 0.9 — Agent Docker Build Context Alignment Rules

This rule applies only to Phase 0.9.

## Scope

Phase 0.9 is limited to standardizing agent Docker build contexts and preventing import errors (`ModuleNotFoundError` for `agents.*` packages) inside FastAPI agent containers.

Primary import paths that must work inside containers:

* `agents.shared.*`
* `agents.coordinator.*`
* `agents.sales.*`
* `agents.content.*`
* `agents.support.*`

Agent services in scope:

* `coordinator-agent`
* `sales-agent`
* `content-agent`
* `support-agent`

## Allowed changes

Allowed files to create or update:

* `docker-compose.yml`
* `agents/**/Dockerfile`
* `agents/**/__init__.py`, only if package initialization is missing and required
* `agents/**/.dockerignore`, only if useful and safe
* `README.md`, only if agent container startup documentation needs a small update
* `docs/phases/step-0.9.md`
* `.cursor/rules/phase-0-9-agent-docker-context.mdc`

## Required outcome

All four agent containers must build and start without Python import errors related to:

* missing `agents` package
* missing `agents.shared`
* missing per-agent package modules
* inconsistent Docker build contexts
* inconsistent `PYTHONPATH`

## Constraints

Do not implement new agent business logic.

Do not implement real LLM behavior.

Do not add or modify `/run` workflow behavior unless it is strictly necessary to keep existing placeholder endpoints import-safe.

**Do not add development bind mounts or hot reload configuration in this phase. That belongs to Phase 0.10.**

**Do not perform final Phase 0 verification or sign-off in this phase. That belongs to Phase 0.11.**

Do not redesign nginx routing.

Do not add new application healthchecks except for preserving existing Phase 0.8 healthchecks if needed.

Do not introduce Prestia-specific behavior.

Do not remove service boundaries. Each agent must remain a separate FastAPI service/container.

## Preferred implementation approach

Prefer a consistent Docker strategy for all agent services:

* Use the repository root as Docker build context for agent services.
* Point each service to its own Dockerfile under `agents/<agent>/Dockerfile`.
* Copy the required `agents/` package tree (shared + per-agent code) into the image.
* Set `WORKDIR` to `/app` and `PYTHONPATH=/app` so imports resolve as `agents.*`.
* Keep container `uvicorn` commands aligned with actual module paths (e.g. `agents.sales.app.main:app`).

Avoid one-off fixes for only one agent if the same structure applies to all agents.

## Documentation expectations

`docs/phases/step-0.9.md` must document:

* Goal
* Scope
* Files created or updated
* Previous problem or risk
* Final Docker build context strategy
* Import paths verified
* Validation commands
* Known limitations
* What was intentionally left for Phase 0.10 and Phase 0.11

Phase 0.9 does not close Phase 0 by itself. Phase 0.10 (dev bind mounts / hot reload) and Phase 0.11 (final verification and sign-off) remain required.
